64enum class CoverageMode {
65 // Make use of existing information in feedback vectors on the heap.
66 // Only return a yes/no result. Optimization and GC are not affected.
67 // Collecting best effort coverage does not reset counters.
68 kBestEffort,
69 // Disable optimization and prevent feedback vectors from being garbage
70 // collected in order to preserve precise invocation counts. Collecting
71 // precise count coverage resets counters to get incremental updates.
72 kPreciseCount,
73 // We are only interested in a yes/no result for the function. Optimization
74 // and GC can be allowed once a function has been invoked. Collecting
75 // precise binary coverage resets counters for incremental updates.
76 kPreciseBinary,
77 // Similar to the precise coverage modes but provides coverage at a
78 // lower granularity. Design doc: goo.gl/lA2swZ.
79 kBlockCount,
80 kBlockBinary,
81};

94class ConsoleCallArguments {
95 public:
96 int Length() const { return length_; }
101 V8_INLINE v8::Local<v8::Value> operator[](int i) const {
102 // values_ points to the first argument.
103 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Undefined(GetIsolate());
104 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(values_);
105 return Local<Value>::FromSlot(values_ + i);
106 }
107
108 V8_INLINE v8::Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
109
110 explicit ConsoleCallArguments(const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>&);
111 explicit ConsoleCallArguments(internal::Isolate* isolate,
112 const internal::BuiltinArguments&);
113
114 private:
115 v8::Isolate* isolate_;
116 internal::Address* values_;
117 int length_;
118};
